From 7e1cbe4ff61670fec4a09b987ae2ad33495da1d4 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Daniel van Vugt <daniel.van.vugt@canonical.com>
Date: Thu, 10 Sep 2020 16:34:53 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 4/6] clutter/frame-clock: Add triple buffering support

This is classical triple buffering with one frame higher latency than
double buffering. But we'll improve on that in the next commit...
---
 clutter/clutter/clutter-frame-clock.c | 100 ++++++++++++++++++++------
 1 file changed, 79 insertions(+), 21 deletions(-)

diff --git a/clutter/clutter/clutter-frame-clock.c b/clutter/clutter/clutter-frame-clock.c
